      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey can u explain how a cold front actually forms? like what's happening with the air masses and what kind of weather should i expect once it hits?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A cold front forms when a colder air mass moves into an area occupied by a warmer air mass. The denser cold air pushes underneath the lighter warm air, causing the warm air to rise. As the warm air rises, it cools and condenses, forming clouds and often leading to precipitation. Once the cold front passes, you can expect cooler temperatures, clear skies, and sometimes a sharp drop in temperature. You might also see gusty winds as the two air masses collide. Just remember, cold fronts can sometimes bring about a sudden change in weather, so it's always good to stay prepared!",
